properties.Name: CustomerCountryOfCitizenship
properties.Description:
The country of citizenship of the customer as of the associated time.

This answers the question "What country(s) does the individual have citizenship for?"

Columns.Name: CustomerId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a Customer.

Columns.Name: CountryId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of the Country.

Columns.Name: PeriodStartDate
Columns.Description: The period start date that the customer has citizenship in the associated country.

Columns.Name: PeriodEndDate
Columns.Description: The period end date that the customer has citizenship in the associated country.

Columns.Name: NationalId
Columns.Description:
The unique national identifier or citizenship ID of the individual in the associated country.

The number typically consists of alphanumeric characters and is not a 'number' but rather an 'ID'.

Columns.Name: PassportId
Columns.Description:
The unique passport identifier or ID of the individual in the associated country.

The number typically consists of alphanumeric characters and is not a 'number' but rather an 'ID'.

Columns.Name: CitizenshipTypeId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a citizenship type.
